Mayor Herman Mashaba has reinstated member of the mayoral committee (MMC) for health Mpho Phalatse, who was suspended earlier this month for public comments in support of Israel made on behalf of the City of Johannesburg In a statement early on Thursday morning, Mashaba said Phalatse has been reinstated with conditions, following an investigation. The reinstatement is effective from 28 June. “The multi-party government has concluded its assessment and engagements surrounding the remarks made by MMC Mpho Phalatse on 10 June 2018,” the statement read. Phalatse, who has already made a public apology, is set to be publicly reprimanded for her remarks in name of the City of Johannesburg. “As the Executive Mayor for the City of Johannesburg, I have spoken to MMC Phalatse and I am appreciative that she is remorseful for the impact of her remarks,” Mashaba said. READ MORE: Joburg Mayor Mashaba suspends Health MMC over pro-Israel comments Phalatse had reportedly said: “I would like to declare that I am a friend of Israel, and the city of Johannesburg is a friend of Israel! Shalom Shalom!” – African News Agency